916","Fordington, Lincoln, England":"Fordington, Lincolnshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Crawford, Lanarkshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Scotland":"Schotland"},"en":{"ABT 1126–":"about 1126–Deceased","1129–1168":"1129–1168","1148–1200":"1148–1200","1126–Female":"1126–Deceased","1129":"1129","1126":"1126","1148":"1148","1168":"1168","1200":"1200","ABT 1147":"about 1147","ABT 1126":"about 1126","about 1148":"about 1148","27 JUN 1916":"27 June 1916","22 NOV 1916":"22 November 1916","Fordington, Lincoln, England":"Fordington, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Lindsay","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Lindsey in Lincolnshire, England. This is first found in the form <i>Lindissi</i>, apparently a derivative of the British name of   Lincoln  . To this was later added the Old English element <i>ēg</i> ‘island’, since the place was virtually cut off by the surrounding fenland. The surname was taken to Scotland at an early date and is the name of an important and powerful Scottish family.","Irish: adopted as an equivalent ofvarious Gaelic names (see   Lindsey  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Linzy","meanings":["Altered form of Scottish, Irish, or English   Lindsay   or   Lindsey  . Compare   Lenzy  ."]},{"name":"Linzey","meanings":["English: variant of   Lindsay   or   Lindsey  ."]},{"name":"Lindsey","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Lindsay  .","Irish: shortened and Anglicized form of various Gaelic surnames, as for example <b>Ó Loingsigh</b> (see   Lynch   1), <b>Mac Giolla Fhionntóg</b> (see   McClintock  ), and <b>Ó Fhloinn</b> (see   Flynn   and   Lynn  )."]},{"name":"Lincoln","meanings":["English: habitational name from the city of Lincoln, so named from an original British name <i>Lindo-</i> ‘lake’ + Latin <i>colonia</i> ‘settlement, colony’. The place was an important administrative center during the Roman occupation of Britain and in the Middle Ages it was a center for the manufacture of cloth, including the famous ‘Lincoln green’.","African American: adoption of the surname in 1 above, in honor of Abraham Lincoln, the 16th president of the US, who abolished slavery.","History: Abraham Lincoln (1809–65), 16th president of the US, was the son of an illiterate laborer, descended from Samuel Lincoln, who had emigrated from England to MA in 1637."]},{"name":"Linsey","meanings":["Scottish, Irish, or English: variant of   Lindsay   or   Lindsey  .","Americanized form of German   Linse   or Swiss German <b>Linsi</b>, see   Lins  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lindsay Mrs. was born about 1126, in Fordington, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Walter de Lindsay about 1147, in Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"ABT 1126–":"umbes 1126–Surnud","1129–1168":"1129–1168","1148–1200":"1148–1200","1126–Female":"1126–Surnud","1129":"1129","1126":"1126","1148":"1148","1168":"1168","1200":"1200","ABT 1147":"umbes 1147","ABT 1126":"umbes 1126","about 1148":"umbes 1148","27 JUN 1916":"27. juuni 1916","22 NOV 1916":"22. november 1916","Fordington, Lincoln, England":"Fordington, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Crawford, Lanarkshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"ABT 1126–":"noin 1126–Kuollut","1129–1168":"1129–1168","1148–1200":"1148–1200","1126–Female":"1126–Kuollut","1129":"1129","1126":"1126","1148":"1148","1168":"1168","1200":"1200","ABT 1147":"noin 1147","ABT 1126":"noin 1126","about 1148":"noin 1148","27 JUN 1916":"27. kesäkuuta 1916","22 NOV 1916":"22. marraskuuta 1916","Fordington, Lincoln, England":"Fordington, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Crawford, Lanarkshire, Skotla